arm_group.description: GnRh, HMG, HCG, Progesterone 45 patients had ultrasound guided embryo transfer during ICSI
GnRh, HMG, HCG, Progesterone 45 patients had embryo transfer using clinical touch technique during ICSI

brief_summary.textblock:
To assess the effect of transabdominal ultrasound guided embryo transfer on the pregnancy
      rates versus clinical touch technique

clinical_study.brief_title: Effect of Ultrasound Guided Embryo Transfer on Pregnancy Rates

detailed_description.textblock:
A total of 90 patients undergoing treatment with ICSI were divided into 2 groups: group 1
      (45 patients), had ultrasound guided embryo transfer and group 2 (45 patients), underwent
      embryo transfer using the clinical touch technique

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age (20-39)

          -  Male factor infertility

          -  Ovarian factor infertility

          -  Unexplained infertility

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Tubal factor infertility

          -  Endometriosis

          -  FSH > 16 iu/l on cycle day 3

          -  Less than 2 embryos grade A

          -  Difficult embryo transfer

intervention.description: GnRh analogue (0.05 mg/day), HMG (150-300 iu/day), HCG (5000 iu/day), Progesterone (100 mg/day)

clinical_study.keyword: Embryo transfer, transabdominal ultrasound, IVF, ICSI

facility.name: IVF Unit, Ain Shams Maternity Hospital, Ain Shams University

clinical_study.official_title: Effect of Ultrasound Guided Embryo Transfer on Pregnancy Rates

primary_outcome.measure: To assess clinical pregnancy rates after using ultrasound guided embryo transfer

reference.citation: Coroleu B, Barri PN, Carreras O, Belil I, Buxaderas R, Veiga A, Balasch J. Effect of using an echogenic catheter for ultrasound-guided embryo transfer in an IVF programme: a prospective, randomized, controlled study. Hum Reprod. 2006 Jul;21(7):1809-15. Epub 2006 Mar 23.
